This project integrates wxWidgets with Ruby and Bowline.
The public API documentation is in the Bowline project:
  http://github.com/maccman/bowline

* OSX only (for the moment) due to  wx/html/webkit.h
* uses wxWidgets 2.9
* uses Ruby 1.9
* uses the Rice 1.3.0 gem (http://github.com/jameskilton/rice)

You'll need to statically compile Ruby and wxWidgets:

  Ruby 1.9.1 configuration:
    ./configure --with-static-linked-ext --program-suffix=19 --prefix=/usr/local

  wxWidgets configuration:
    ./configure --disable-shared
    
Run rake to compile.




Building WebKit on OSX:

Edit WebCore/Configurations/
 Remove reference to EXTERNAL_SYMBOLS
 Say no to strip code
 Say no to dead code
 Remove umbrella
 Remove visibility-inlines-hidden
 
 Edit JavaScriptCore/Configurations/
  Remove reference to EXTERNAL_SYMBOLS
  Say no to strip code
  Say no to dead code
  Disable ENABLE_DASHBOARD_SUPPORT
 
Edit WebKitTools/Scripts/check-for-weak-vtables
 Comment out
 
Edit WebKitTools/Scripts/build-webkit
 Remove WebKit from projects
